						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in the garden adjoining the tank at Chauḷikēri.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇadēvarāya, 1514 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This right side of the slab bearing this record is completely damaged and chipped off. It registers a gift of land to a deity and for feeding some Brāhmaṇas. It refers to Lakshmīnārāyaṇa, probably the deity, and mentions that <hi rend="bold">Vijaya • • • .,</hi> son of a certain <hi rend="bold">Voḍeya</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 143[7], Bhāva, Chaitra śu. 1, Monday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1514 A.D., March 27.</hi> The Śaka year was current.</p>						

						</summary>
